{"type":"message","id":"35a88e6c","parentId":"c3974922","timestamp":"2026-03-19T21:26:46.892Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_dd0f361b-6749-4d57-874a-759bcccef507","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/BROWSER_RELAY_SETUP.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":577,"output":80,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":657,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773955606892}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a45e324","parentId":"35a88e6c","timestamp":"2026-03-19T21:26:46.910Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_dd0f361b-6749-4d57-874a-759bcccef507","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Browser Relay Setup — Fixed 2026-03-19\n\n## The Problem\n\"Profile not found\" errors because `defaultProfile` was set to `\"chrome\"` which didn't exist.\n\n## The Fix\n**Remove `defaultProfile`** from openclaw.json. Never add it back.\n\n## How It Works\n\n### Architecture\n1. **WSL Gateway** runs a relay server on port 18792\n2. **Windows Chrome** has the OpenClaw extension installed\n3. Extension connects to WSL relay → I can control your Windows Chrome\n\n### Install Chrome Extension (one-time)\n```bash\n# In WSL:\nopenclaw browser extension install\n# Shows path like: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/browser/chrome-extension\n\n# In Windows Chrome:\n# 1. Go to chrome://extensions\n# 2. Enable \"Developer mode\"\n# 3. \"Load unpacked\" → select the path above\n# 4. Pin the extension\n# 5. Click extension icon to attach/detach tabs\n```\n\n### Always Use This Command Format\n```bash\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay <command>\n```\n\n### Commands\n```bash\n# Check status\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay status\n\n# Take screenshot\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\n\n# Navigate\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate https://example.com\n\n# List profiles\nopenclaw browser profiles\n```\n\n## Current Working Config (openclaw.json)\n```json\n{\n  \"browser\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"executablePath\": \"/usr/bin/chromium-browser\",\n    \"headless\": true,\n    \"noSandbox\": true,\n    \"profiles\": {\n      \"openclaw\": {\n        \"cdpPort\": 18800,\n        \"color\": \"#FF69B4\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"relayBindHost\": \"0.0.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key:** No `defaultProfile` field — that's the secret.\n\n## If Something Breaks\n1. Run `openclaw browser profiles` — check what profiles are visible\n2. If chrome-relay shows but commands fail → restart gateway: `openclaw gateway restart`\n3. Check port 18792 is listening: `ss -tlnp | grep 18792`\n\n## Backup Files\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — working config (Mar 19 15:43)"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773955606908}}
