{"type":"message","id":"f9eec4bd","parentId":"c1ff0ec7","timestamp":"2026-03-19T21:26:57.407Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_12305870-fa4c-4bcd-9688-0f3cd9d2ff90","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-19 — Session Emergency Compact\n\n## ⚠️ SESSION AT MAX CAPACITY — COMPACTING NOW\n\n## What's Been Done Today\n\n### Skills & Tools\n- ✅ `linkedin-writer` installed (workspace/skills/linkedin-writer) — Security: CLEAN, MIT-0, no API keys needed\n- ✅ Brave API key working — web search ✅\n- ✅ Chrome relay profile (`chrome-relay`) working — 1920×804 real desktop browser confirmed\n- ✅ `defaultProfile` changed from \"chrome\" (broken) to \"chrome-relay\"\n- ✅ Backed up openclaw.json + MEMORY.md + daily memory before all changes\n\n### Skills Researched (NOT installed)\n- `google-docs` — Hold: routes through Maton.ai third-party gateway, \"Warnings: yes\" flag, OAuth via ctrl.maton.ai. Needs further review before trust.\n- `browser-automation` — Skip: SUSPICIOUS flag on Clawhub\n- `skill-creator` on Clawhub — Skip: SUSPICIOUS flag. Use built-in version at ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n\n### Browser Relay Status\n- `chrome-relay` running on port 18792 ✅\n- Multiple profiles possible (chrome-relay-personal, chrome-relay-work) on different ports for simultaneous multi-profile control\n- Extension path: `~/.openclaw/browser/chrome-extension` — load unpacked in Chrome Dev Mode\n- One extension instance = one WebSocket connection = one Chrome profile at a time\n\n### Configuration Fix Applied\n- `browser.defaultProfile` changed from \"chrome\" (didn't exist) to \"chrome-relay\"\n\n---\n\n## NAVA CONTENT SYSTEM — FULL STATE\n\n### What's Built (All in workspace/rag/)\n- 3 ready drafts: 001 (Cost Ontology), 002 (LTC Targeting), 011 (Relationship-First)\n- LinkedIn + X derivatives for each\n- Image direction notes for each\n- Full RAG corpus: 22 articles, 1741 chunks, BM25 + vector index\n- Synthesis documents: Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md, Nava_Contradiction_Gap_Matrix_v1.md\n- Idea bank: 12 ideas\n- Queue pack: rag/QUEUE_PACK.md — ordered priority list\n\n### Nava Agent Plan (NOT YET BUILT)\n- Separate agent via `openclaw agents add nava`\n- Own workspace, own memory, own skills\n- Dawn (me) keeps coordinator role + summary of what Nava does\n- Paul Sial = Nava boss (look up for context)\n- Bindings: WhatsApp messages about Nava → nava agent\n\n---\n\n## SPLIT-BRAIN PROBLEM\n\n**Root cause:** One agent (main), three independent sessions (TUI, WhatsApp, WebUI) with no shared context. Session at 869KB when this hit.\n\n**Fix plan:**\n1. Set up Nava agent (isolated workspace + corpus)\n2. Set up AbroadWorks agent (isolated workspace — AbroadWorks is parent company, Nava is a client)\n3. Dawn = coordinator, routes to correct agent\n4. Each agent has own channel binding\n\n---\n\n## OPEN ISSUES / DEFERRED\n\n| Item | Status | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| Gemma3 role-alternation 400 errors | Deferred | Direct API works, OpenClaw message format issue |\n| Google Docs skill | Hold | Maton.ai third-party gateway — needs review |\n| Windows Chrome relay (multi-profile) | Deferred | Different CDP ports per profile |\n| Gmail/email access | Future | himalaya skill exists, Google Workspace |\n| Gemini access | Future | gemini built-in skill needs API key |\n| Memory 14-day window | Config option | `compaction.memoryFlush` tuning |\n| Persistent Chrome profile for login | Deferred | `browser.profiles.openclaw.userDataDir` config needed |\n| LinkedIn browsing (for voice calibration) | Deferred | Needs login + persistent session |\n| TUI/WebUI tutorial | Future | Schedule walkthrough session |\n\n---\n\n## About Tiny\n- Risk averse: requires reading SKILL.md before any install\n- Prefers concise responses\n- Wants pushback over agreeability\n- Content workflow: concept → post-first or image-first → LinkedIn → X → optional FB\n- Model: minimax-m2.7:cloud primary, nemotron fallback\n- No OpenAI tokens — using Ollama cloud models\n\n## About Paul Sial\n- Tiny's boss at AbroadWorks\n- Nava is a client of AbroadWorks\n- Paul and Tiny consider Tiny's articles \"well-written\"\n- Tiny wants to understand what makes content perform better\n\n## About Dawn (me)\n- Coordinator agent role\n- Retains: personal context, preferences, coordination logic\n- Does NOT retain: Nava corpus (goes to Nava agent), posting cadence details\n- Role: route, delegate, coordinate across agents\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773955617405}}
