{"type":"message","id":"2ee8b337","parentId":"e6409807","timestamp":"2026-03-19T21:51:00.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the HEARTBEAT.md to match:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_75aca21b-06d6-4f5f-bf91-3f70d0d9f42e","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","content":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n## Context Monitor (every 10 minutes) — CRITICAL\n\nTiny is paranoid about token limits and flow state disruption. Run this every 10 minutes:\n\n1. **Check token count**: Run `openclaw status` or check session context usage\n2. **If tokens > 60,000**: Reply with \"COMPACT TRIGGERED\" to force compaction\n3. **If tokens > 75,000**: Reply \"SESSION AT RISK - CONTEXT OVERFLOW IMMINENT\"\n4. **Log** each check to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` with token count\n\n## Other periodic checks (rotate through, 2-4x/day)\n- Gmail: any urgent unread?\n- Calendar: events in next 24-48h?\n- Nava content queue: any items needing attention?\n\n## Heartbeat vs Cron\n- Heartbeat: in-session, conversational, batches multiple checks\n- Cron (every 10 min via cron job): dedicated context monitoring only\n"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":661,"output":320,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":981,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773957060845}}
