{"type":"message","id":"020179fc","parentId":"8d17ba54","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:32:17.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done and committed.\n\nOn the draft itself — here's the closer with the \"different\" repetition actually fixed:\n\n> We get it. As former healthcare executives, we were frustrated each time an early resignation cost us time and money. We built Nava with a different philosophy — not a different payment model, but a fundamentally different approach.\n\nThree \"different\" in four sentences. Let me try rewriting it:\n\n> We get it. As former healthcare executives, we were frustrated each time an early resignation cost us time and money. We built Nava around a different philosophy — not how we charge, but how we align.\n\nThat's two \"different\" — one is structurally needed, one is the philosophy noun. Still not clean. What if:\n\n> We get it. As former healthcare executives, we were frustrated each time an early resignation cost us time and money. We built Nava to solve that — not with a new payment model, but with a fundamentally new approach.\n\nNo repetition. \"New\" and \"fundamentally\" do the work. Does that capture what you wanted?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":341,"output":253,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":594,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773959537440}}
