{"type":"message","id":"63ad2a76","parentId":"1667d726","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:51:04.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right. LTC is the primary market for international nurse recruitment. NurseSphere = international pipeline + relational model. LTC facilities are the ones who need it most. That's a direct fit.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d9afa7ca-fb91-49d6-85b4-00b938e1306e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport os\n\n# Read all fragments that might mention NurseSphere or LTC\nfragments = [\"143f2fb3.txt\", \"8f1be070.txt\", \"d9011790.txt\"]\n\nfor frag in fragments:\n    path = f\"rag/clean_txt/{frag}\"\n    if os.path.exists(path):\n        with open(path) as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        if \"nursesphere\" in content.lower() or \"ltc\" in content.lower() or \"long-term\" in content.lower():\n            print(f\"\\n=== {frag} ===\")\n            print(content[:1500])\nPY"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":303,"output":296,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":599,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773960664266}}
{"type":"message","id":"34af317f","parentId":"63ad2a76","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:51:04.304Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d9afa7ca-fb91-49d6-85b4-00b938e1306e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 143f2fb3.txt ===\nSpecialized Healthcare Staffing Solutions for Long-Term Care & Assisted Living Facilities\nRunning a long-term care or assisted living facility means juggling resident needs, staff well-being, regulatory demands, and family expectations all at once. The pressure is constant, and the stakes are deeply personal. Residents depend on consistency. Families expect compassion. Your team needs the support to deliver both.\nAt Nava Healthcare, Our origin story started out of the dire needs we personally experienced while operating in this industry, and therefore we work closely with administrators and facility leaders to provide staff who bring the right mix of experience, reliability, and empathy. From floor nurses and CNAs to clinical leadership and support staff, we help you maintain stable coverage without compromising the continuity your residents deserve.\nStaffing\nlong-term care\nand assisted living means working against constant disruption. Turnover is high. Callouts happen with little notice. Acuity levels change overnight. And the work isn’t easy. Your team needs the stamina and emotional presence to support residents day in and day out. Not everyone can do it well, and not every clinician belongs in this environment. The added strain of meeting regulatory requirements while operating short only raises the stakes. Missed shifts and weekend gaps compromise care and wear down your core team. That’s why the right staffing partner matters.\nWe understand the coordination it takes to \n\n=== 8f1be070.txt ===\nSupporting Non-Profits and Community Health Centers with Smart, Compliant, and Compassionate Staffing Solutions\nAt Nava Healthcare, we specialize in community health center staffing, supporting nonprofit organizations with flexible hiring solutions and a deep understanding of your mission.\nBalancing care delivery\nwith limited resources is never simple. Tight budgets, unpredictable patient flow, and high turnover are part of daily life all while staying focused on delivering quality care to underserved populations. Finding professionals who share your values and can contribute from day one is no small task. That’s where we come in.\nOur approach is built for the realities of community-based care. From short-term support to long-term placements, we align with your clinical and operational goals without compromising what matters most: your commitment to the communities you serve.\nWe focus on mission-aligned professionals who understand the demands of high-need settings. Every candidate is vetted not just for their experience, but for their ability to thrive in environments where empathy, adaptability, and cultural awareness are essential. From front-desk coordinators to advanced practice providers, we staff both clinical and administrative roles with people who reflect your mission and help strengthen the care you deliver.\nWe support every part of your facility, from the exam room to the front desk to the broader community. Our clinical placements include physicians, nurse practi"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"=== 143f2fb3.txt ===\nSpecialized Healthcare Staffing Solutions for Long-Term Care & Assisted Living Facilities\nRunning a long-term care or assisted living facility means juggling resident needs, staff well-being, regulatory demands, and family expectations all at once. The pressure is constant, and the stakes are deeply personal. Residents depend on consistency. Families expect compassion. Your team needs the support to deliver both.\nAt Nava Healthcare, Our origin story started out of the dire needs we personally experienced while operating in this industry, and therefore we work closely with administrators and facility leaders to provide staff who bring the right mix of experience, reliability, and empathy. From floor nurses and CNAs to clinical leadership and support staff, we help you maintain stable coverage without compromising the continuity your residents deserve.\nStaffing\nlong-term care\nand assisted living means working against constant disruption. Turnover is high. Callouts happen with little notice. Acuity levels change overnight. And the work isn’t easy. Your team needs the stamina and emotional presence to support residents day in and day out. Not everyone can do it well, and not every clinician belongs in this environment. The added strain of meeting regulatory requirements while operating short only raises the stakes. Missed shifts and weekend gaps compromise care and wear down your core team. That’s why the right staffing partner matters.\nWe understand the coordination it takes to \n\n=== 8f1be070.txt ===\nSupporting Non-Profits and Community Health Centers with Smart, Compliant, and Compassionate Staffing Solutions\nAt Nava Healthcare, we specialize in community health center staffing, supporting nonprofit organizations with flexible hiring solutions and a deep understanding of your mission.\nBalancing care delivery\nwith limited resources is never simple. Tight budgets, unpredictable patient flow, and high turnover are part of daily life all while staying focused on delivering quality care to underserved populations. Finding professionals who share your values and can contribute from day one is no small task. That’s where we come in.\nOur approach is built for the realities of community-based care. From short-term support to long-term placements, we align with your clinical and operational goals without compromising what matters most: your commitment to the communities you serve.\nWe focus on mission-aligned professionals who understand the demands of high-need settings. Every candidate is vetted not just for their experience, but for their ability to thrive in environments where empathy, adaptability, and cultural awareness are essential. From front-desk coordinators to advanced practice providers, we staff both clinical and administrative roles with people who reflect your mission and help strengthen the care you deliver.\nWe support every part of your facility, from the exam room to the front desk to the broader community. Our clinical placements include physicians, nurse practi","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773960664301}}
{"type":"message","id":"042af724","parentId":"34af317f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:51:21.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. So the post is Idea 002 refranded through the NurseSphere lens — LTC facilities running short, and NurseSphere is the international pipeline that actually solves it.\n\nThat's a strong post concept. LTC is the highest-need, shortest-staffed segment. International recruitment via NurseSphere directly addresses the root cause — not enough domestic clinicians to fill the gaps.\n\n**The structure writes itself:**\n1. The problem: LTC is running short, call-outs, turnover, regulatory pressure\n2. Why traditional recruitment fails: reactive, local pool, high cost, no loyalty\n3. NurseSphere: international pipeline + relational model = stable, long-term staff\n4. Nava positioning\n\n**What I need from you to proceed:** What's the hook? What's the angle that makes an LTC operator stop scrolling?\n\nOptions:\n- **\"You can't recruit your way out of this\"** — reactive hiring is the trap\n- **\"The staffing model your competitors use\"** — implies others already solving it this way\n- **Something else you've seen in the data**\n\nWhat's the opening line?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":805,"output":449,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":1254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773960681532}}
{"type":"message","id":"7bc454ea","parentId":"042af724","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:59:15.325Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 00:59 GMT+2] We are taking a different approach here. I am about to teach you new things so I need you to proactively take notes as we progress. The process is important and you will need to understand the full process before you attempt to create an agent. It is also likely that we will not complete this today, so I need you to make some changes to your heartbeat.\n\nIf I am active, your heartbeat should be set to 10 minutes. During your heartbeat, do compaction and save your memories. Remember, backups are only on request or if we are about to make config changes. Additionally, do backups when I signoff for the night - I will typically tell you I'm going to bed but if it's late and I have not been active for over an hour, assume I have signed off.\n\nIf I am inactive, even during the day, meaning 2-3 heartbeats came without my direct input, slow your heartbeat to 30 minutes unless instructed otherwise. When inactive, you need not save memories or compact unless you are actively working on an assignmet. If working on an assignment, 10 minute-heartbeats, memory saves, and compaction still applies. Also, if the assignment is complex, you may have to increase your heartbeat to every 5 minutes. Does this make sense?"}],"timestamp":1773961155321}}
{"type":"message","id":"303552a0","parentId":"7bc454ea","timestamp":"2026-03-19T22:59:36.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes sense. Let me update the heartbeat rules:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_5441593a-db33-4b1f-8ec2-fa2895cdba78","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n## Context Monitor — Tin's Rules (2026-03-20)\n\n### Heartbeat intervals\n| Situation | Interval | Actions |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Active** — user input within last 2-3 heartbeats | 10 min | Compact + save memory |\n| **Inactive** — no user input for 2-3 heartbeats | 30 min | Nothing unless assigned |\n| **Assignment active** — working on a task for user | 10 min | Compact + save memory |\n| **Complex assignment** | 5 min | Compact + save memory |\n| **User signs off** (says going to bed, or silent after 23:00 + 1h inactive) | — | Backup before sleeping |\n\n### During compaction\n- Check token count\n- If >60k: trigger explicit compact message\n- If >75k: warn \"SESSION AT RISK - CONTEXT OVERFLOW IMMINENT\"\n- Log each check to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n\n### Backups\n- Only on request OR before config changes OR when user signs off\n- NOT during normal heartbeat cycles\n- `mkdir -p ~/TinyBackUp/$(date +%Y%m%d)` then copy relevant files\n\n### Active learning protocol (2026-03-20)\nTiny is teaching about NurseSphere / LTC process. Take notes in `memory/2026-03-20.md` as we go. This is for building the Nava agent — process knowledge is as important as content rules.\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":49747,"output":574,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50321,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773961176401}}
