{"type":"message","id":"5020b185","parentId":"9f4b9208","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:06:40.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. The main tools:\n\n- **StealthWriter.ai** — claims not designed for academic dishonesty\n- **BypassGPT** — 50+ languages, free tier\n- **HumanizeAI.pro** — SEO keyword retention\n- **HIX Bypass** — from the HIX writer ecosystem\n- **WriteHuman.ai** — targets GPTZero, Copyleaks, ZeroGPT\n- **GPTHuman** — 80 languages, 99.9% success rate claim\n- **Rewritify.ai** — free option\n\nAll work the same way: paste AI text → get rewritten version that bypasses detection. None are local/OFFLINE — they all require cloud submission.\n\nFor Tiny's workflow, the relevant concern is LinkedIn's AI-detection friction, not academic plagiarism. LinkedIn doesn't visibly flag AI content to readers — but the concern seems to be more about authenticity and LinkedIn's algorithm possibly down-ranking stuff that looks templated.\n\nThe real question: does he want to run AI drafts through a humanizer *before* revising them? Or is the humanizer for after the revision pass?\n\nI'll note the tools and ask when he's ready to show me the next step.\n\n**Logged to memory — updated process notes:**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_4c597c38-31d0-4b67-b7b0-7c5200ef3697","name":"edit","arguments":{"newString":"### Humanizer tools (researched 2026-03-20)\nUsed to rewrite AI-drafted text to bypass AI detection (GPTZero, Originality AI, Turnitin, Winston AI).\nTools: StealthWriter.ai, BypassGPT, HumanizeAI.pro, HIX Bypass, WriteHuman.ai, GPTHuman, Rewritify.ai.\nNone are offline — all require cloud submission.\nPurpose in Tiny's workflow: TBD — awaiting next step in process teaching.","oldString":"### Draft 001 revision (2026-03-19 evening)","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":2587,"output":521,"cac