{"type":"message","id":"7f03d727","parentId":"4070c6d2","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:16:00.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I used `ls -la` which shows modification time, not creation time. You're right to call it out.\n\nLooking at actual timestamps — the folder has files from earlier today, but these two are newly added during this session:\n\n- **`Nava Healthcare Content Bible.docx`** — added at 01:41\n- **`ROLE & KNOWLEDGE BASE.md`** — added at 01:43\n\nBoth were created after this session started (~01:00). Everything else in the folder was already there from earlier today.\n\nThat's my error — I made an assumption without checking the timestamps properly. Won't happen again."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":869,"output":382,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":1251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773962160522}}
