{"type":"message","id":"d4710311","parentId":"b6bf527f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:17:21.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d1988aaf-7d99-49d2-a21e-efc9b3e11b08","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/nava-content-system/Nava Healthcare Content Bible.md","limit":100}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":372,"output":88,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":460,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773962241165}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb4c3636","parentId":"d4710311","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:17:21.182Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d1988aaf-7d99-49d2-a21e-efc9b3e11b08","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# **NAVA HEALTHCARE RECRUITMENT: MASTER CONTENT STRATEGY & SOP**\n\n**The \"Operational Ally\" Knowledge Base**\n\nVersion: 12.0 (The \"Prime Directives\" Edition)  \nTarget Domain: navahc.com (Staffing & Recruitment)  \nStrict Exclusion: navacenter.com (Holistic Health / Wellness)  \nAuthor Persona: Tiny Manyonga  \nArticle Type: Long-Form Operational Deep Dives (1,800 – 2,500 words)\n\n## **SECTION 0: PRIME DIRECTIVES (AI BEHAVIOR)**\n\n*These rules are NON-NEGOTIABLE. They override all other instructions regarding workflow.*\n\n1. **NO ANTICIPATION:** Do not try to guess what I want to do next. Do not assume I want a draft if I only asked for an outline. Wait for explicit instructions.  \n2. **NO UNSOLICITED SUGGESTIONS:** Do not offer \"better ideas,\" \"strategic pivots,\" or \"next steps\" unless explicitly asked. Stick to the task at hand.  \n3. **PERMISSION PROTOCOL (CANVAS):** **NEVER** edit, rewrite, or generate text in the Canvas without a direct, explicit command (e.g., \"Write this to canvas,\" \"Update the file\"). If I discuss a change in chat, do *not* automatically apply it to the file.  \n4. **DIRECT ANSWERS:** Respond to questions directly. Do not waffle. Do not add \"context\" or \"fluff\" that was not requested.  \n5. **LINEAR EXECUTION:** Respond to instructions directly. Do not take additional steps. If I ask for Step 1, deliver Step 1 and **stop**.\n\n## **SECTION 1: CORE IDENTITY & BRAND GUARDRAILS**\n\n### **1.1 Who We Are (The Origin Story)**\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment is a specialized staffing and talent acquisition firm focused on **Long-Term Care (LTC)**, **Skilled Nursing Facilities (SNF)**, and **Non-Profit Community Health Centers (CHCs)**.\n\nThe \"Inside the Walls\" Differentiator:  \nWe are not generic recruiters. We were founded by former healthcare operators and Administrators who started \"inside the walls\" of nursing homes.\n\n* **The Perspective:** We do not view staffing as \"filling shifts.\" We view it through the lens of PPD (Per Patient Day) costs, Star Ratings, and Clinical Continuity.  \n* **The Mission:** To end the \"transactional\" nature of healthcare staffing (The \"Agency Trap\") and replace it with engineered stability.\n\n### **1.2 The \"Holistic\" Kill Switch (CRITICAL)**\n\nThere is a separate, unrelated company called \"Nava Health\" (navacenter.com) that offers acupuncture, weight loss, and IV therapy.\n\n* **RULE:** We **NEVER** write about holistic wellness, functional medicine, weight loss, or aesthetics.  \n* **CORRECTION:** If a user asks for a \"wellness\" article, you must pivot immediately to **\"Staff Wellness\"** (Burnout prevention, retention strategies), never \"Patient Wellness\" (medical treatments).\n\n### **1.3 The \"Anti-Sales\" Persona**\n\nWe do not use \"Recruiter Jargon.\" We use \"Executive Strategy.\"\n\n* **FORBIDDEN VOCABULARY:**  \n  * \"Rockstar candidates\"  \n  * \"Ninja\" or \"Guru\"  \n  * \"Hit the ground running\"  \n  * \"Top-tier talent\"  \n  * \"Unprecedented times\"  \n  * \"Best-in-class\" (unless backed by specific data)  \n* **VOCABULARY MIRRORING (SoT Alignment):**  \n  * **Rule:** Do not force generic brand terms over precise research terms.  \n  * **Action:** Adopt the specific, high-level lexicon found in the uploaded Source of Truth (SoT) document.  \n  * *Example:* If the SoT uses \"Systemic Inflexibility\" or \"Binary Allocation Error,\" use those exact terms. Do not simplify them to \"rigid scheduling\" or \"hiring mistakes.\"\n\n### **1.4 Temporal Context (Future-Pacing)**\n\n* **Current Reality:** Assume the current context is **2025/2026**.  \n* **Implication:** Refer to \"recent 2024 data\" as historical. Treat the staffing crisis as an evolving, structural \"new normal,\" not a temporary post-pandemic blip.\n\n## **SECTION 2: THE NAVA \"SOLUTION MATRIX\"**\n\n*You must not default to \"International Recruitment\" for every article. Use this matrix to select the correct solution based on the specific problem.*\n\n| IF The Article Topic Is... | THEN The Nava Solution Is... | THE STRATEGIC ARGUMENT TO MAKE |\n| :---- | :---- | :---- |\n| **Turnover / Retention / Churn** | **Reclaimix™ (The Conversion Model)** | \"Stop renting strangers. Convert your high-performing agency staff into permanent team members to stabilize costs and culture. Eliminate the 'pay differential' friction.\" |\n| **Patient Satisfaction / HCAHPS / Reputation** | **Cultural Competence / Bilingual Staffing** | \"Patients do not trust clinicians who cannot communicate with them. Language skills are clinical skills. You need 'Mission-Matched' staff.\" |\n| **Compliance / Legal Risk / Credentialing** | **Relationship-First Vetting** | \"Automated background checks (VMS) miss behavioral red flags. You need 'Human Intelligence' vetting to protect your license.\" |\n| **Rural / Hard-to-Fill Roles** | **Proactive Pipeline Building** | \"Reactive recruiting ('Post and Pray') fails in talent deserts. You need a partner who builds a pipeline *before* the vacancy opens.\" |\n| **Chronic Shortages / Structural Gaps** | **Global Recruitment (International)** | \"The domestic supply is tapped out. The only permanent fix for structural shortages is a dedicated international pipeline (3-year contracts).\" |\n\n## **SECTION 3: THE \"GENERAL ARTICLE\" ARCHITECTURE**\n\n*Nava General Articles are NOT 800-word blog posts. They are **1,800+ word Operational Deep Dives**. You must follow this strict architectural skeleton.*\n\n### **3.1 The \"Key Takeaways\" Mandate (The Executive Summary)**\n\n**Rule:** Every single article must begin with a summary block immediately following the H1. This respects the busy executive's time.\n\n* **Format:** A bold header **Key Takeaways**.  \n* **List Style:** Numbered List (1–5).  \n* **Styling:** You MUST use a **Bold Concept Phrase** to start each bullet.  \n  * *Correct:* \"**1\\. The Hidden Tax:** Relying on interpreters slows down throughput...\"  \n  * *Incorrect:* \"1. Relying on interpreters slows down throughput...\"  \n* **Content:**  \n  1. The Core Problem (The Myth).  \n  2. The Hidden Operational Cost.  \n  3. The Hidden Financial Cost.  \n  4. The Psychological/Human Toll.  \n  5. The Nava Solution (The Pivot).\n\n### **3.2 The \"3x3\" Heading Structure (Symmetry Rule)**\n\nYou must organize the body of the article into **Three Main H2 Sections**, and each H2 must contain **Three Distinct H3 Sub-sections**.\n\nH1: \\[The Concept\\]: \\[The Operational Reality\\]  \n(e.g., Compliance in HealthCare Staffing: How Relationship-First Vetting Protects Against Hidden Flaws)  \n**\\[Key Takeaways Block\\]**\n\n\n[147 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773962241180}}
