{"type":"message","id":"bba848df","parentId":"76256abe","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:53:15.138Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_529bc0e6-c45e-4949-9129-105974f4a4b1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\n\nwith open(\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Try to find any text that looks like LinkedIn post content\n# Look for text between specific markers\ntext_blocks = re.findall(r'(?:We wrote about|The truth about|Here\\'s why|Most healthcare|If you|Inside)[^\\n]{50,200}', html, re.IGNORECASE)\n\nprint(f\"Found {len(text_blocks)} potential post blocks\")\nfor i, block in enumerate(text_blocks[:15]):\n    print(f\"\\n--- BLOCK {i+1} ---\")\n    print(block[:500])\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":56274,"output":219,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964395137}}
{"type":"message","id":"69783031","parentId":"bba848df","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:53:15.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_529bc0e6-c45e-4949-9129-105974f4a4b1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found 23 potential post blocks\n\n--- BLOCK 1 ---\nIf you're looking for healthcare recruiters who understand both sides of the table employers and candidates.\n\n--- BLOCK 2 ---\nIf you are filling schedule gaps with unvetted \"warm bodies\" who don't fit your culture, or pushing your core staff to the breaking point, your marketing budget is being incinerated in real-time.<br><br>In \n\n--- BLOCK 3 ---\nIf you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr, why can't you just pay your own staff $60/hr?\"<br><br>It is the most common accusation thrown at healthcare leaders. On social media, it is framed as greed.\n\n--- BLOCK 4 ---\nif you could recapture that premium without the agency? There is a structural model that allows facilities to do exactly that. We call it 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗺𝗶𝘅.<br><br>And we will be talking a lot more about it soon.<b\n\n--- BLOCK 5 ---\nIf you hire your emergency team for a sunny day🌞🌞🌞, they, too, will need rescuing when the storm lands⛈️⛈️⛈️. <br><br>As leaders, we often write job descriptions for the facility we 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘳𝘶𝘯: the one tha\n\n--- BLOCK 6 ---\nIf you are in a crisis, a renovation, or a turnaround, don't hire the candidate who looks good on the PDF. 𝗛𝗶𝗿𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝘄𝗵𝗼 𝗹𝗼𝗼𝗸𝘀 𝗴𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗶𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘂𝗱.<br><br><a class=\"_39fb1c9c _3f77afa9\" href=\"https://www.lin\n\n--- BLOCK 7 ---\nIf you want your talented staff to stay, it starts with cultural and environmental fit.<br><br>We break down why retention is the only recruitment metric that actually protects your units and financial heal\n\n--- BLOCK 8 ---\nIf you aren't diagnosing the disease, you can't prevent it.<br><br>We break down the full anatomy of clinician turnover—and how to stop the bleeding—in our latest article.<br><br>👉 Read \"The Anatomy of a Cl\n\n--- BLOCK 9 ---\nIf you missed the target, the advice was always: \"Do 𝘮𝘰𝘳𝘦\". <br><br>Being told to simply \"do more\" was demoralising. We were burning through leads and annoying prospects just to hit an activity metric.<br><\n\n--- BLOCK 10 ---\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \"Urgent Needs,\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \"quality candidates.\"<br><br>Recruitme\n\n--- BLOCK 11 ---\nif you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b\n\n--- BLOCK 12 ---\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \"Urgent Needs,\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \"quality candidates.\"<br><br>Recruitme\n\n--- BLOCK 13 ---\nif you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b\n\n--- BLOCK 14 ---\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \"Urgent Needs,\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \"quality candidates.\"<br><br>Recruitme\n\n--- BLOCK 15 ---\nif you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":330,"aggregated":"Found 23 potential post blocks\n\n--- BLOCK 1 ---\nIf you're looking for healthcare recruiters who understand both sides of the table employers and candidates.\n\n--- BLOCK 2 ---\nIf you are filling schedule gaps with unvetted \"warm bodies\" who don't fit your culture, or pushing your core staff to the b