at this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b\n\n--- BLOCK 12 ---\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \"Urgent Needs,\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \"quality candidates.\"<br><br>Recruitme\n\n--- BLOCK 13 ---\nif you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b\n\n--- BLOCK 14 ---\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \"Urgent Needs,\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \"quality candidates.\"<br><br>Recruitme\n\n--- BLOCK 15 ---\nif you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \"transactional\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.<b","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773964395473}}
