{"type":"message","id":"77c7e958","parentId":"3849e0c5","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:56:21.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_4e2d7642-2e2d-4f77-8a8a-88747409723a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\nwith open(\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Find the post starting with \"Patients read billboards\"\nmatch = re.search(r'Patients read billboards.{100,600}', html, re.IGNORECASE)\nif match:\n    text = match.group(0)\n    # Clean up HTML\n    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)\n    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text)\n    print(text)\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":59284,"output":188,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59472,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964581588}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e16773a","parentId":"77c7e958","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:56:21.674Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_4e2d7642-2e2d-4f77-8a8a-88747409723a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room. A 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans. I always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hospital for an interview, get a feel for the chaos on the floor, and just quietly decide to take an offer somewhere else? They look at the ratios, they spot the exhaustion in the eyes of your core staff."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":81,"aggregated":"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room. A 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans. I always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hospital for an interview, get a feel for the chaos on the floor, and just quietly decide to take an offer somewhere else? They look at the ratios, they spot the exhaustion in the eyes of your core staff.","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773964581672}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1f10bae","parentId":"5e16773a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:56:26.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_1b469ce3-151c-47d5-b6fc-a31aacfe1acc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\nwith open(\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Find posts with \"Patients read\" or the $100/hr frame\nposts = re.findall(r'(Patients read billboards.{200,400}|If you can afford to pay an agency nurse.{200,400}|If you hire your emergency team for a sunny day.{200,400})', html, re.IGNORECASE)\n\nfor i, post in enumerate(posts):\n    # Clean HTML\n    clean = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', post)\n    clean = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', clean)\n    print(f\"\\n--- POST {i+1} ---\")\n    print(clean)\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":59281,"output":257,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59538,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964586380}}
{"type":"message","id":"226c636d","parentId":"c1f10bae","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:56:26.676Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_1b469ce3-151c-47d5-b6fc-a31aacfe1acc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"--- POST 1 ---\nPatients read billboards, but clinicians read the room. A 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans. I always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hosp\n\n--- POST 2 ---\nIf you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr, why can't you just pay your own staff $60/hr?\" It is the most common accusation thrown at healthcare leaders. On social media, it is framed as greed. In the boardroom, we know it is 𝗪𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻. Here is the math that the \"Agency vs. Staff\" debate ignores: 𝟭. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 \"𝗕𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗥𝗮𝘁𝗲\" 𝗜𝗹𝗹𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 🎭 First, let’s kill the myth: The agency nurse is not pocketing that full $100/h\n\n--- POST 3 ---\nIf you hire your emergency team for a sunny day🌞🌞🌞, they, too, will need rescuing when the storm lands⛈️⛈️⛈️. As leaders, we often write job descriptions for the facility we 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘳𝘶𝘯: the one that is fully staffed, quiet, and operating perfectly with an occasional emergency or moment of chaos. But we usually need to hire for the facility we actually run 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. We recently helped a client in Alabama who was in the middle of a"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":287,"aggregated":"--- POST 1 ---\nPatients read billboards, but clinicians read the room. A 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans. I always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hosp\n\n--- POST 2 ---\nIf you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr, why can't you just pay your own staff $60/hr?\" It is the most common accusation thrown at healthcare leaders. On social media, it is framed as greed. In the boardroom, we know it is 𝗪𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻. Here is the math that the \"Agency vs. Staff\" debate ignores: 𝟭. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 \"𝗕𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗥𝗮𝘁𝗲\" 𝗜𝗹𝗹𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 🎭 First, let’s kill the myth: The agency nurse is not pocketing that full $100/h\n\n--- POST 3 ---\nIf you hire your emergency team for a sunny day🌞🌞🌞, they, too, will need rescuing when the storm lands⛈️⛈️⛈️. As leaders, we often write job descriptions for the facility we 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘳𝘶𝘯: the one that is fully staffed, quiet, and operating perfectly with an occasional emergency or moment of chaos. But we usually need to hire for the facility we actually run 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. We recently helped a client in Alabama who was in the middle of a","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773964586673}}
{"type":"message","id":"2fc937bd","parentId":"226c636d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:56:32.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right — that one is gold. Full post:\n\n> \"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room. A 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans. I always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hospital for an interview, get a feel for the chaos on the floor, and just quietly decide to take an offer somewhere else? They look at the ratios, they spot the exhaustion in the eyes of your core staff.\"\n\nThat's written BY Tiny FOR Yosef — same voice as Draft 001. The \"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room\" pivot is exactly the kind of bold narrative move that works on LinkedIn.\n\nThese posts (including the $100/$60 wage compression one, and the sunny day/emergency team one) are the model I should be learning from for future Drafts.\n\nThat's my error — my regex missed it because of how the HTML was structured. I should have scraped more thoroughly."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":58341,"output":287,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58628,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964592281}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb09abc1","parentId":"2fc937bd","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:58:03.147Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 01:58 GMT+2] The next one after that starts with \"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom, and the narrative is the same: \"𝘐𝘧 𝘢𝘥𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘵𝘩𝘦 $100/𝘩𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘺 𝘱𝘢𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘨𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘶𝘴, 𝘸𝘦 𝘸𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘣𝘦 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘳𝘵-𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘥.\"\" Did you also miss that?"}],"timestamp":1773964683145}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a92e121","parentId":"fb09abc1","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:58:15.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d00ce4ef-59b1-4724-82af-7e681fe2ca6b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\nwith open(\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Find posts starting with \"Walk into any\"\nposts = re.findall(r'Walk into any healthcare facility[^.]{50,400}', html, re.IGNORECASE)\n\nfor i, post in enumerate(posts):\n    clean = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', post)\n    clean = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', clean)\n    print(f\"\\n--- POST {i+1} ---\")\n    print(clean[:600])\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":60100,"output":719,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60819,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964695821}}
