{"type":"message","id":"f031c5e4","parentId":"27d9369c","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:58:24.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_53b7f5cd-e4a0-43ee-9e8b-af634f26d514","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\nwith open(\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Look for the full $100/hr post - it should have the \"Wage Compression\" breakdown\nmatch = re.search(r'Walk into any healthcare facility.{800,2000}', html, re.IGNORECASE)\nif match:\n    text = match.group(0)\n    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)\n    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text)\n    print(text)\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":59674,"output":215,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59889,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964704359}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fc91303","parentId":"f031c5e4","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:58:24.439Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_53b7f5cd-e4a0-43ee-9e8b-af634f26d514","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom, and the narrative is the same: \"𝘐𝘧 𝘢𝘥𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘵𝘩𝘦 $100/𝘩𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘺 𝘱𝘢𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘨𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘶𝘴, 𝘸𝘦 𝘸𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘣𝘦 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘳𝘵-𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘥.\" To the staff, it looks like indifference, or even callousness. It feels demoralizing to watch a stranger get paid double while your loyalty is ignored (even if they are splitting that hourly with an agency). But having sat in the executive chair, I know what it looks like from the other side: 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗧𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗽. When you are looking at the P&amp;L, you are often staring at a brutal choice: &nbsp;1. Hire 10 Agency Nurses at a premium (Variable Cost). &nbsp;2. Raise the base rate to attract 10 Staff Nurses (Fixed Cost). The math is unforgiving. Because of union step-scales or rigid pay bands, raising the Start Rate for those 10 new hires often legally triggers a pay reset for hundreds of existing clinicians. I’ve seen the models where the cost of the agency contract was $2M, but the cost of the system-wide pay reset was $15M. Administrators don't sign that agency contract because they don't value their staff. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝘀𝗶𝗴𝗻 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗮 𝗳𝗶𝘅𝗲𝗱-𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘄𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗵𝗼𝘀𝗽𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗱𝗼𝗼𝗿𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝟴 𝗺𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗵𝘀. We need to stop villainizing leaders for doing the only math that keeps the lights on. We also need to give them a better tool than the agency. The smartest systems are now building Internal Resource Pools that capture the flexibility of the agency without the middleman markup. You don't need to break your pay scale. You just need to own the mechanism. 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆 𝘄𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝗶𝗹𝘁 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗺𝗶𝘅. Watch this space... #HealthcareLeadership <a class=\"_39fb1c9c _3f77afa9\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/all/?keywords=%2"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":74,"aggregated":"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom, and the narrative is the same: \"𝘐𝘧 𝘢𝘥𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘵𝘩𝘦 $100/𝘩𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘺 𝘱𝘢𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘨𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘶𝘴, 𝘸𝘦 𝘸𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘣𝘦 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘳𝘵-𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘥.\" To the staff, it looks like indifference, or even callousness. It feels demoralizing to watch a stranger get paid double while your loyalty is ignored (even if they are splitting that hourly with an agency). But having sat in the executive chair, I know what it looks like from the other side: 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗧𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗽. When you are looking at the P&amp;L, you are often staring at a brutal choice: &nbsp;1. Hire 10 Agency Nurses at a premium (Variable Cost). &nbsp;2. Raise the base rate to attract 10 Staff Nurses (Fixed Cost). The math is unforgiving. Because of union step-scales or rigid pay bands, raising the Start Rate for those 10 new hires often legally triggers a pay reset for hundreds of existing clinicians. I’ve seen the models where the cost of the agency contract was $2M, but the cost of the system-wide pay reset was $15M. Administrators don't sign that agency contract because they don't value their staff. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝘀𝗶𝗴𝗻 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗮 𝗳𝗶𝘅𝗲𝗱-𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘄𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗵𝗼𝘀𝗽𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗱𝗼𝗼𝗿𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝟴 𝗺𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗵𝘀. We need to stop villainizing leaders for doing the only math that keeps the lights on. We also need to give them a better tool than the agency. The smartest systems are now building Internal Resource Pools that capture the flexibility of the agency without the middleman markup. You don't need to break your pay scale. You just need to own the mechanism. 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆 𝘄𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝗶𝗹𝘁 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗺𝗶𝘅. Watch this space... #HealthcareLeadership <a class=\"_39fb1c9c _3f77afa9\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/all/?keywords=%2","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773964704437}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfaa3fe7","parentId":"1fc91303","timestamp":"2026-03-19T23:58:30.892Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it — full post:\n\n> \"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom, and the narrative is the same: 'If administration just took the $100/hr they pay the agency and gave it to us, we wouldn't be short-staffed.' To the staff, it looks like indifference... But having sat in the executive chair, I know what it looks like from the other side: **The Tenure Trap.** When you are looking at the P&L, you are often staring at a brutal choice: Hire 10 Agency Nurses at a premium (Variable Cost) vs. Raise the base rate to attract 10 Staff Nurses (Fixed Cost)... I've seen the models where the cost of the agency contract was $2M, but the cost of the system-wide pay reset was $15M. Administrators don't sign that agency contract because they don't value their staff. **They sign it because a fixed-cost explosion would close the hospital doors in 8 months.** ... We need to give them a better tool than the agency. That's why we built **Reclaimix.**\"\n\nThis is the pattern I should learn from:\n\n1. **Hook** — \"Walk into any breakroom...\" (relatable, in-the-room opening)\n2. **Acknowledge both sides** — staff feel ignored, but admins face a math problem\n3. **Explain the hidden mechanism** — Tenure Trap, pay reset cascades\n4. **Introduce solution** — Reclaimix at the end\n\nSame structure as \"Patients read billboards\" — pivot, context, solution.\n\nThat's 3 posts from Tiny-for-Yosef that I should have captured. My scraping was incomplete."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":59949,"output":487,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773964710890}}
{"type":"message","id":"9830a302","parentId":"dfaa3fe7","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:03:29.476Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 02:03 GMT+2] \"We saved a client over $𝟲𝟬,𝟬𝟬𝟬 recently. Not through a sales call or getting them a new deal. We did it by making a phone call they didn't know they needed.\" That's the start of another one and it's linking to a Nava post that starts with \"𝗳 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗲 𝗮 \"𝗷𝗼𝗯 𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝘀𝗰𝗿𝗮𝗽𝗲𝗿\" 𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝘀 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗻𝗲𝗿, 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻'𝘁 𝗯𝗲 𝘀𝘂𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲𝘀 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗼𝗼𝗿. And when that door spins fast, it's easier to blame the people than diagnose the problem.\n\"\n\n\nThen there is a repost of my post that I wrote, \"I remember when I got my first job. I was so excited, but boy, was it an eye-opener. \" - On that I shared a Nava post that starts with \"𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗶𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴𝗹𝗲 𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗯𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗹𝗲 𝘁𝗼 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗳𝗮𝗰𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗮 𝗰𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗻 𝘀𝗵𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗮𝗴𝗲, 𝗯𝘂𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗽𝗿𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀? \". I know RegEx and I don't think it is appropriate here. I think maybe you should run the saved page through Gemma or something! And can you look into browsing tools because if you cant do simple clicking and scrolling then what's the point? This is Yosef's profile, figure it out! https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/recent-activity/all/"}],"timestamp":1773965009473}}
