{"type":"message","id":"b760ce0d","parentId":"2de7c479","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:04:10.505Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. You're right — I should have used Gemma on the HTML file directly instead of trying to parse it with regex.\n\n**What I did find:**\n\n**\"We saved a client over $60,000\"** (full post):\n> \"We saved a client over $60,000 recently. Not through a sales call or getting them a new deal. We did it by making a phone call they didn't know they needed. We were doing a routine check-in with a new star clinician when she told us, 'I love the job, but I'm resigning next Thursday.' The facility had no idea; they were about to be blindsided. The reason? Her son's high school graduation was at 5:00 PM. She needed to leave her shift 2 hours early. The facility's handbook stated clearly: 'New employees don't qualify for PTO'... Everyone acted rationally. And it was about to cost the facility a fortune. But we caught wind of the situation, intervened and called the CFO directly.\"\n\nThis is another Tiny-for-Yosef original — same voice, same structure.\n\n**What I missed:**\n- The \"job board scraper\" post (partial: \"job boards, scan for valid qualifications, and shove them into your inbox to hit a commission target...\")\n- \"I remember when I got my first job...\"\n- The repost of Tiny's post about hiring practices\n\n**On browsing tools:** You're right — the current relay can't click and scroll properly. I need to look into this. The tmux skill might give me better interactive control. Let me check what's available:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_4b60736e-5d43-4bf3-9e96-445dc6f85e3f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/tmux/SKILL.md","limit":50}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":61674,"output":584,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62258,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRea