{"type":"message","id":"3bfaa1e0","parentId":"b760ce0d","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:04:10.524Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_4b60736e-5d43-4bf3-9e96-445dc6f85e3f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: tmux\ndescription: Remote-control tmux sessions for interactive CLIs by sending keystrokes and scraping pane output.\nmetadata:\n  { \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"🧵\", \"os\": [\"darwin\", \"linux\"], \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"tmux\"] } } }\n---\n\n# tmux Session Control\n\nControl tmux sessions by sending keystrokes and reading output. Essential for managing Claude Code sessions.\n\n## When to Use\n\n✅ **USE this skill when:**\n\n- Monitoring Claude/Codex sessions in tmux\n- Sending input to interactive terminal applications\n- Scraping output from long-running processes in tmux\n- Navigating tmux panes/windows programmatically\n- Checking on background work in existing sessions\n\n## When NOT to Use\n\n❌ **DON'T use this skill when:**\n\n- Running one-off shell commands → use `exec` tool directly\n- Starting new background processes → use `exec` with `background:true`\n- Non-interactive scripts → use `exec` tool\n- The process isn't in tmux\n- You need to create a new tmux session → use `exec` with `tmux new-session`\n\n## Example Sessions\n\n| Session                 | Purpose                     |\n| ----------------------- | --------------------------- |\n| `shared`                | Primary interactive session |\n| `worker-2` - `worker-8` | Parallel worker sessions    |\n\n## Common Commands\n\n### List Sessions\n\n```bash\ntmux list-sessions\ntmux ls\n```\n\n### Capture Output\n\n```bash\n\n[104 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773965050522}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3dc88de","parentId":"3bfaa1e0","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:04:24.058Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_46ae877c-9631-485f-9e89-4bcc6e6400d6","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md","old_string":"### Next immediate action\n1. Derive X post from Draft 001\n2. Await Yosef profile scroll capability or Tiny's summary of Yosef's post patterns","new_string":"### Yosef's LinkedIn posts (scraped from HTML dump)\n\nThese are posts WRITTEN BY TINY FOR YOSEF — model posts for future Nava content:\n\n1. **\"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room\"**\n   - Hook: Patients vs clinicians perception gap\n   - Pivot: marketing slogans don't fool clinicians\n   - Message: elite nurses spot exhaustion during interviews\n   - Source: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568 (this is Draft 001 - posted to Nava, not Yosef's personal)\n\n2. **\"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom...\"** ($100/hr wage compression)\n   - Hook: breakroom narrative about admin not sharing agency premium\n   - Acknowledge both sides: staff feels ignored, admins face math problem\n   - Mechanism: The Tenure Trap — raising start rates triggers system-wide pay reset\n   - Solution: Reclaimix / Internal Resource Pools\n   - Full post: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/yosef-roston_the-tenure-trap-healthcare-leaders-healthcare-recruiting-posted-by-yosef-7327544042933395456\n\n3. **\"We saved a client over $60,000\"**\n   - Hook: saved $60k through a phone call, not a sales pitch\n   - Story: star clinician resigning over son's graduation — handbook said \"new employees don't qualify for PTO\"\n   - Nava intervention: called CFO directly, resolved\n   - Message: retention economics > policy technicalities\n\n4. **\"If you hire your emergency team for a sunny day...\"**\n   - Hook: sunny day hiring vs crisis hiring\n   - Message: hire for the facility you run TODAY, not the one you want\n   - Full post captured\n\n5. **\"If you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr...\"**\n   - Hook: $100/hr question to admins\n   - Mechanism: Wage Compression breakdown\n   - Full post captured\n\n6. **\"If you aren't diagnosing the disease, you can't prevent it\"**\n   - Hook: turnover anatomy article CTA\n\n7. **\"If you missed the target, the advice was always: Do more\"**\n   - Hook: critique of activity-based recruiting metrics\n\n8. **\"If you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game\"**\n   - Hook: anti-transactional recruitment model\n\n### Browser tool limitation\nCurrent OpenClaw browser relay cannot reliably scroll or click. Must use HTML dump + Gemma or find better browsing tool. Tiny frustrated by this limitation — fixing is priority.\n\n### Next immediate action\n1. Derive X post from Draft 001 (Nava LinkedIn → X mandatory, was missed)\n2. Investigate browser scrolling tools"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":61349,"output":834,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62183,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773965064058}}
