{"type":"message","id":"96cda745","parentId":"8b8a24f9","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:07:03.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oh! Now I get it:\n\n- The **Nava agent** I'm building needs to handle **BOTH**\n  - **LinkedIn posts** (short-form, our style rules)\n  - **Blog articles** (long-form, Content Bible system)\n\nThe files you added are the **blog article system** that I need to learn so the agent can do both. That's why you said \"the agent you will create should be capable of writing both LinkedIn posts like the one we created and blogs for the website.\"\n\nSo maybe:\n- One agent that knows both systems\n- OR two agents (LinkedIn agent + Blog agent)\n\nGot it this time. Let me update memory:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_a47ec32e-3a60-4e20-8f74-5b18db5114a5","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md","old_string":"### Content system distinction (critical)\n**LinkedIn posts** (short-form):\n- Governed by: Tiny's writing style rules formalized 2026-03-20\n- Process: concept discussion → decide image-first or post-first → draft → Nava LinkedIn → X → optional channels\n- Length: 1-3 paragraphs, flowing prose, compressed sentences\n- Do NOT apply blog architecture rules here\n\n**Blog articles** (long-form, 1,800–2,500 words):\n- Governed by: Nava Healthcare Content Bible v12\n- Process: 3x3 structure (3 H2s × 3 H3s), Key Takeaways block, SoT ingestion, outline first then draft\n- These are operational deep dives, NOT LinkedIn posts\n- Tiny's custom GPT uses these — not the LinkedIn writing style rules\n- The agent must handle BOTH but apply the correct rules per output type","new_string":"### Content system distinction (critical)\n**Nava agent must handle BOTH workflows:**\n\n**LinkedIn posts** (short-form):\n- Governed by: Tiny's writing style rules formalized 2026-03-20\n- Process: concept discussion → decide image-first or post-first → draft → Nava LinkedIn → X → optional channels\n- Length: 1-3 paragraphs, flowing prose, compressed sentences\n- Examples: Draft 001 \"The Incentive Trap\", Yosef posts like \"Patients read billboards\"\n\n**Blog articles** (long-form, 1,800–2,500 words):\n- Governed by: Nava Healthcare Content Bible v12\n- Process: 3x3 structure (3 H2s × 3 H3s), Key Takeaways block, SoT ingestion, outline first then draft\n- These are operational deep dives, NOT LinkedIn posts\n- Content Bible shows the blog system that Tiny's custom GPT uses\n\n**Agent architecture options:**\n1. Single agent trained on BOTH systems (knows when to apply which)\n2. Two separate agents: LinkedIn agent + Blog agent"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":62961,"output":763,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63724,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773965223393}}
{"type":"message","id":"22598b55","parentId":"96cda745","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:07:03.411Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_a47ec32e-3a60-4e20-8f74-5b18db5114a5","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  82 ### Step 1 (known): Research angle + H1s\n  83 Tiny thinks of a research angle and potential H1s. Files to be shared.\n  84 \n  85 ### Content system distinction (critical)\n+ 86 **Nava agent must handle BOTH workflows:**\n+ 87 \n  86 **LinkedIn posts** (short-form):\n  87 - Governed by: Tiny's writing style rules formalized 2026-03-20\n  88 - Process: concept discussion → decide image-first or post-first → draft → Nava LinkedIn → X → optional channels\n  89 - Length: 1-3 paragraphs, flowing prose, compressed sentences\n- 90 - Do NOT apply blog architecture rules here\n+ 92 - Examples: Draft 001 \"The Incentive Trap\", Yosef posts like \"Patients read billboards\"\n  91 \n  92 **Blog articles** (long-form, 1,800–2,500 words):\n  93 - Governed by: Nava Healthcare Content Bible v12\n  94 - Process: 3x3 structure (3 H2s × 3 H3s), Key Takeaways block, SoT ingestion, outline first then draft\n  95 - These are operational deep dives, NOT LinkedIn posts\n- 96 - Tiny's custom GPT uses these — not the LinkedIn writing style rules\n- 97 - The agent must handle BOTH but apply the correct rules per output type\n+ 98 - Content Bible shows the blog system that Tiny's custom GPT uses\n+ 99 \n+100 **Agent architecture options:**\n+101 1. Single agent trained on BOTH systems (knows when to apply which)\n+102 2. Two separate agents: LinkedIn agent + Blog agent\n  98 # 2026-03-20\n  99 \n 100 ## 01:40 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n 101 - Core scope (crawl → synthesis → full RAG): COMPLETE/STABLE\n     ...","firstChangedLine":86},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773965223408}}
