{"type":"message","id":"f68779b9","parentId":"ff12becc","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:12:10.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_7a26827e-7b52-45b4-ab69-c31f017944d2","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md","old_string":"### Yosef's LinkedIn posts (scraped from HTML dump)\n\nThese are posts WRITTEN BY TINY FOR YOSEF — model posts for future Nava content:\n\n1. **\"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room\"**\n   - Hook: Patients vs clinicians perception gap\n   - Pivot: marketing slogans don't fool clinicians\n   - Message: elite nurses spot exhaustion during interviews\n   - NOTE: Similar to Draft 001 \"The Incentive Trap\" but different post\n\n2. **\"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom...\"** ($100/hr wage compression)\n   - Hook: breakroom narrative about admin not sharing agency premium\n   - Acknowledge both sides: staff feels ignored, admins face math problem\n   - Mechanism: The Tenure Trap — raising start rates triggers system-wide pay reset\n   - Solution: Reclaimix / Internal Resource Pools\n   - Full post: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/yosef-roston_the-tenure-trap-healthcare-leaders-healthcare-recruiting-posted-by-yosef-7327544042933395456\n\n3. **\"We saved a client over $60,000\"**\n   - Hook: saved $60k through a phone call, not a sales pitch\n   - Story: star clinician resigning over son's graduation — handbook said \"new employees don't qualify for PTO\"\n   - Nava intervention: called CFO directly, resolved\n   - Message: retention economics > policy technicalities\n\n4. **\"If you hire your emergency team for a sunny day...\"**\n   - Hook: sunny day hiring vs crisis hiring\n   - Message: hire for the facility you run TODAY, not the one you want\n   - Full post captured\n\n5. **\"If you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr...\"**\n   - Hook: $100/hr question to admins\n   - Mechanism: Wage Compression breakdown\n   - Full post captured\n\n6. **\"If you aren't diagnosing the disease, you can't prevent it\"**\n   - Hook: turnover anatomy article CTA\n\n7. **\"If you missed the target, the advice was always: Do more\"**\n   - Hook: critique of activity-based recruiting metrics\n\n8. **\"If you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game\"**\n   - Hook: anti-transactional recruitment model","new_string":"### Yosef's LinkedIn posts (FULL LIST from Gemma scraping HTML dump)\n\n**Status: NEEDS SORTING** — need to identify which are:\n- Original by Yosef\n- Reposts from Tiny (tinymanyonga)\n- Reposts from Nava LinkedIn (nava-healthcare)\n\n**Media Posts (products):**\n- NurseSphere: The Long-Term Solution to Your Nursing Shortage\n- Reclaimix: Reclaim Costs. Reclaim Talent. Reclaim Stability.\n\n**Activity Posts (12 total):**\n\n1. **\"Patients read billboards, but clinicians read the room\"** (3w)\n   - Brand/Employer Brand angle\n   - Link to article: https://lnkd.in/dXuv7BdE\n   - STATUS: TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF (see earlier capture)\n\n2. **\"It takes 6 months and millions to approve a hospital rebranding...\"** (3w)\n   - Brand Gap: Employer Brand = leading indicator of Patient Brand\n   - Link to article: https://lnkd.in/dXuv7BdE\n   - STATUS: LIKELY TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF\n\n3. **\"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom...\"** (2mo)\n   - The Tenure Trap / Wage Compression\n   - Solution: Reclaimix\n   - STATUS: TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF (captured in full earlier)\n\n4. **\"The Unsolvable Algebra of Healthcare Staffing\"** (2mo)\n   - $100/hr vs $60/hr breakdown\n   - Bill Rate Illusion, Step Scale Handcuffs, Fixed-Cost Explosion\n   - Solution: Reclaimix\n   - STATUS: TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF\n\n5. **\"If you hire your emergency team for a sunny day...\"** (3mo)\n   - Chaos Tolerance hiring\n   - Story: Greg the maintenance director in Alabama\n   - STATUS: TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF\n\n6. **\"90% of recruitment focuses on the What...\"** (3mo)\n   - Context Gap: What (skills) vs Where (environment) vs When (timing)\n   - Link to article: https://lnkd.in/dD422E4B\n   - STATUS: UNKNOWN - could be original or repost\n\n7. **\"We saved a client over $60,000\"** (3mo)\n   - Retention story: graduation PTO case\n   - STATUS: TINY WROTE THIS FOR YOSEF\n\n8. **\"If you hire a job board scraper...\"** (3mo)\n   - Turnover anatomy: Unavoidable vs Transactional vs Systemic\n   - Link to article: https://lnkd.in/dWibV3Hm\n   - STATUS: UNKNOWN\n\n9. **\"Most recruitment agencies are just expensive mail-sorting services\"** (3mo)\n   - Nava philosophy: operational not marketing problem\n   - Announcement: shifting to resource content vs job posts\n   - STATUS: LIKELY ORIGINAL YOSEF (philosophy/mission)\n\n**Reposts to identify:**\n- Posts from tinymanyonga (Tiny's personal profile)\n- Posts from Nava LinkedIn page"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":52793,"output":1353,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773965530077}}
