{"type":"message","id":"19932065","parentId":"7b419049","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:14:47.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The HTML dump doesn't make it easy to distinguish reposts. The \"reposted this\" text I found is just UI button labels, not post metadata.\n\n**What I found:**\n- Tiny Manyonga: 7 mentions (mostly in page metadata, not post content)\n- Nava Healthcare: 47 mentions (mostly in post text linking to company)\n- Direct repost indicators: 6 (these are reaction buttons, not post sources)\n\nThe Gemma output showed me 12 \"activity posts\" — but it didn't distinguish which were:\n- Yosef's original content\n- Reposts from Tiny (tinymanyonga)  \n- Reposts from Nava LinkedIn (nava-healthcare)\n\n**Can you tell me:**\n1. Which of the 12 posts are reposts from your personal page?\n2. Which are reposts from Nava's company page?\n\nI can then mark them correctly in memory. Alternatively — if you have an HTML dump of your own activity page (tinymanyonga), I could scrape that to see what you posted that Yosef might have shared."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":59881,"output":363,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773965687338}}
