{"type":"compaction","id":"e7b17077","parentId":"90b8294f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:26:28.974Z","summary":"## Goal\nBuild the Nava content system and agent — combining writing style rules, process knowledge, and product knowledge into a training corpus. The agent must handle BOTH LinkedIn posts AND blog articles (not one or the other).\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- **Screenshot rule (NEW):** \"Check my screenshot\" → Windows folder (`/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`). \"Get a screenshot\" → agent's media folder (`~/.openclaw/media/browser/`). Any screenshot mention → route through Gemma for description\n- **Heartbeat intervals (UPDATED):** Active = 10 min (compact + memory save). Inactive = 30 min (no actions unless assigned). Complex assignment = 5 min. User sign-off = backup first\n- **Grammarly underlines = tool artifact, never authorial intent**\n- **Split-brain:** TUI session and main session do not share context; must use shared workspace files to transfer work between them\n- **Transcripts:** `sessions_history` API truncates at ~15k bytes; raw JSONL files at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/{id}.jsonl` are complete and readable directly\n- **No unsolicited actions:** Must discuss proactive steps with Tiny before taking them — \"no unsolicited actions\" rule violated once during this session\n- **Browser tool limitation:** Current OpenClaw browser relay cannot scroll or click reliably; HTML dump + Gemma workaround needed\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Draft 001 posted to LinkedIn (urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568), saved to `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md`, original AI draft archived\n- [x] Tiny's LinkedIn writing style rules formalized (12 rules) and committed to MEMORY.md\n- [x] Heartbeat rules updated — active/inactive intervals, sign-off backup protocol, complex assignment rule\n- [x] Split-brain problem documented: TUI revisions must go to shared workspace files; session IDs must be provided manually\n- [x] Screenshot workflow confirmed: check my screenshot → Windows folder; get screenshot → agent media folder; any screenshot → Gemma\n- [x] Session notes written to `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- [x] Backup created at `~/TinyBackUp/20260320/`\n- [x] Corpus confirmed: 27 files mention NurseSphere, but only as brand references in nav/footers — no published article explains what NurseSphere actually is or how it works\n- [x] Reclaimix identified: Nava division converting agency nurses in-building to permanent hires (\"No interviews. No onboarding.\")\n- [x] NurseSphere identified: international recruitment program + relational model; mentioned in brand context only in published corpus\n- [x] Yosef's LinkedIn posts extracted from HTML dump (~6-8 posts identified)\n- [x] Agent architecture clarified: agent must do BOTH LinkedIn AND blog articles\n- [x] Proactive error flagged: used browser relay without discussing first\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Tiny teaching research and writing process — notes being captured in `memory/2026-03-20.md` as session progresses\n- [ ] NurseSphere substance (how it works, process, differentiator) not yet in corpus — needs to come from Tiny directly\n- [ ] Draft 002 (LTC facilities + NurseSphere angle) not yet drafted\n- [ ] X post from Draft 001 still missing — workflow gap\n\n### Blocked\n- Cannot draft NurseSphere post without Tiny's process knowledge — corpus has brand mentions only, no substantive content\n- Browser tool cannot scroll — HTML dump workaround used but frustrates Tiny\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Link-to-article CTA chosen over custom image:** Draft 001 uses CTA linking to `navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/`; LinkedIn auto-generates preview image\n- **Post-first over image-first:** Copy carries the post; visual is supporting\n- **NurseSphere ≠ Reclaimix:** Two distinct Nava products — Reclaimix converts agency nurses in-building; NurseSphere is international pipeline + relational model\n- **Draft 002 angle:** LTC facilities running short + NurseSphere as the solution (international recruitment addresses root cause); no published corpus content exists to draft this from — requires Tiny's direct input\n- **Agent architecture:** Single agent trained on BOTH LinkedIn + blog systems, OR two separate agents (LinkedIn agent + Blog agent) — Tiny to decide\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Derive X post from Draft 001 content (Nava LinkedIn → X is mandatory)\n2. Investigate better browser scrolling tools (tmux skill, Playwright, or other)\n3. Continue taking notes as Tiny teaches the research and writing process\n4. Capture NurseSphere substantive content (what it is, how it works, differentiator) for the corpus\n5. Once process is taught, apply it to Draft 002 — LTC facilities angle\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Draft 001 live:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568\n- **Posted drafts:** `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md`\n- **Archived original AI draft:** `rag/drafts/archived_draft_001_v1_ai.md`\n- **Writing rules:** `MEMORY.md` → section \"Tiny's LinkedIn Writing Style Rules (formalized 2026-03-20)\"\n- **Heartbeat config:** `HEARTBEAT.md` (updated), cron job `fe4180d9-037f-413a-a1dd-c7291e5d2729` (10-min interval)\n- **Session notes:** `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- **Backup location:** `~/TinyBackUp/20260320/`\n- **Idea bank:** `rag/idea_bank.md`\n- **Article index:** `rag/article_index.md`\n- **Nava corpus:** `rag/clean_txt/` (26 articles + draft fragments)\n- **Key gap:** No published article explains NurseSphere — only brand-name references in nav bars\n- **Yosef's posts source:** `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html`\n- **Key Yosef posts captured:** \"Patients read billboards\", \"Walk into any healthcare facility breakroom ($100/hr)\", \"We saved a client over $60,000\", \"If you hire your emergency team for a sunny day\", \"If you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr\", \"The Tenure Trap\"\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser asked if the assistant ran an HTML file from Downloads through Gemma. The HTML file is a LinkedIn profile activity page for Yosef Roston that the user wanted processed to extract posts.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant initially used regex instead but then attempted to process the HTML through Gemma (vision model)\n- First tried sending 100KB of HTML content base64-encoded to Gemma via Ollama API - failed with HTTP 500\n- Reduced to 50KB and tried again - also failed with HTTP 500 Internal Server Error\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Assistant then checked available Ollama models to diagnose the issue\n- The curl command to `/api/tags` was executed to see what models are available\n- The response shows gemma3:27b-cloud is among available models (a cloud-hosted Gemma 3 27B model)\n- This was part of troubleshooting why Gemma rejected the image upload request\n\n<read-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/BROWSER_RELAY_SETUP.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-19.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/EMERGENCY_SAVE.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"69fe872d","tokensBefore":65775,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/BROWSER_RELAY_SETUP.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-19.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/EMERGENCY_SAVE.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md","/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md"]},"fromHook":false}
{"type":"message","id":"7f750978","parentId":"e7b17077","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:26:29.059Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 02:25 GMT+2] Yes, but your count of posts seems to be off for the various categories. Furthermore, what insights can you give me about my posts vs Yosef's posts vs Nava posts. Your response should be solely based on the HTML not the corpus or the docs I gave you. This applies only for this prompt and this response."}],"timestamp":1773966389056}}
{"type":"message","id":"38bdefc8","parentId":"7f750978","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:26:38.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e60fb764-c1f7-4f94-838a-521f97a84150","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport base64, json, urllib.request, re\n\nhtml_path = \"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\"\nwith open(html_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html_content = f.read()\n\n# Clean up for text extraction\nhtml_clean = re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', html_content, flags=re.DOTALL | re.IGNORECASE)\nhtml_clean = re.sub(r'<style[^>]*>.*?</style>', '', html_clean, flags=re.DOTALL | re.IGNORECASE)\ntext_only = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', html_clean)\ntext_only = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text_only)\ntruncated = text_only[:50000]\n\nimg_b64 = base64.b64encode(truncated.encode()).decode()\n\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"qwen3.5:cloud\",\n    \"messages\": [{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": f\"\"\"Analyze Yosef Roston's LinkedIn activity page HTML. Count and list ALL posts by original author.\n\nCATEGORIES:\n1. Posts where Yosef is the ORIGINAL AUTHOR (Yosef wrote it himself)\n2. Posts REPOSTED from Tiny Manyonga (Tin's personal profile)\n3. Posts REPOSTED from Nava Healthcare (company page)\n4. Posts REPOSTED from anyone else\n\nFor EACH post, provide:\n- Post number\n- Original author (who wrote it originally)\n- Whether Yosef posted it as himself OR reposted it\n- Brief topic/summary\n\nThen give me TOTALS:\n- Total posts by Yosef (original)\n- Total reposts from Tiny\n- Total reposts from Nava\n- Total reposts from others\n\nText (first 50k chars):\n{truncated}\"\"\"\n    }],\n    \"stream\": False\n}\n\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    \"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\",\n    data=json.dumps(payload).encode(),\n    headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\n\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=180) as r:\n    result = json.loads(r.read())\n    print(result[\"message\"][\"content\"])\nPY","timeout":200}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":38986,"output":593,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39579,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773966398978}}
