{"type":"message","id":"74e0fdb0","parentId":"d7b5d179","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:27:27.537Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_645ebd8a-effb-4a4b-bafd-e74d1bcfd9f8","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the provided HTML text from Yosef Roston's LinkedIn activity page, here is the analysis of all posts found in the content stream.\n\n### POST LIST\n\n**Post 1**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston (Featured Post)\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Promotion of The YoJoeShow Podcast Episode 13 (Uncensored discussion on geopolitics, antisemitism, etc.).\n\n**Post 2**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Healthcare branding vs. clinical culture; argues clinicians see past marketing slogans to the reality of care.\n\n**Post 3**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** The \"Brand Gap\" between marketing promises and internal reality of burned-out units.\n\n**Post 4**\n- **Original Author:** Marquis Health Consulting Services\n- **Type:** Reposted from anyone else\n- **Topic:** American Heart Month; promoting CardioPro program and cardiac care stories.\n\n**Post 5**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** The \"Tenure Trap\" in healthcare staffing; explains why agencies are used over staff pay raises due to fixed-cost explosions.\n\n**Post 6**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** The \"Unsolvable Algebra\" of staffing; explains wage compression and why agency rates don't translate to staff pay raises.\n\n**Post 7**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Hiring for crisis/chaos tolerance; example of placing a maintenance director (\"Greg\") suited for a construction environment.\n\n**Post 8**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Context Gap in recruitment; argues retention depends on environment/timing, not just skills/licenses.\n\n**Post 9**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Retention success story; saving a client $60k by intervening in a PTO policy dispute preventing a nurse's resignation.\n\n**Post 10**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Critique of \"job board scraper\" agencies; discusses turnover buckets (Unavoidable, Transactional, Systemic).\n\n**Post 11**\n- **Original Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n- **Type:** Reposted from Tiny Manyonga\n- **Topic:** Escaping the \"Volume Trap\" in sales/recruitment; advocates for human instinct over AI automation in vetting.\n\n**Post 12**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Critique of transactional recruitment agencies; announces shift to resource-focused content strategy (Video post).\n\n**Post 13**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Same content as Post 12 (Duplicate entry in feed); Critique of transactional recruitment agencies.\n\n**Post 14**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Same content as Post 12/13 (Duplicate entry in feed); Critique of transactional recruitment agencies.\n\n**Post 15**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** Job posting for CNA & Nurses in Montgomery County, AL (Bonus incentives).\n\n**Post 16**\n- **Original Author:** Joe Carvalho\n- **Type:** Reposted from anyone else\n- **Topic:** Aviation careers; promotion of The YoJoeShow Podcast episode regarding North Perry Airport Community Day.\n\n---\n\n### TOTALS\n\n- **Total posts by Yosef (original):** 5\n  *(Includes 1 Featured Post + 4 Activity Feed Posts)*\n- **Total reposts from Tiny:** 1\n- **Total reposts from Nava:** 8\n  *(Includes 3 duplicate entries of the same \"⛔You know what?\" post found in the HTML text)*\n- **Total reposts from others:** 2\n  *(Marquis Health Consulting Services, Joe Carvalho)*\n\n**Grand Total Posts Analyzed:** 16\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"lucky-meadow","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Based on the provided HTML text from Yosef Roston's LinkedIn activity page, here is the analysis of all posts found in the content stream.\n\n### POST LIST\n\n**Post 1**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston (Featured Post)\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Promotion of The YoJoeShow Podcast Episode 13 (Uncensored discussion on geopolitics, antisemitism, etc.).\n\n**Post 2**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** Healthcare branding vs. clinical culture; argues clinicians see past marketing slogans to the reality of care.\n\n**Post 3**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** The \"Brand Gap\" between marketing promises and internal reality of burned-out units.\n\n**Post 4**\n- **Original Author:** Marquis Health Consulting Services\n- **Type:** Reposted from anyone else\n- **Topic:** American Heart Month; promoting CardioPro program and cardiac care stories.\n\n**Post 5**\n- **Original Author:** Yosef Roston\n- **Type:** Original Author (Yosef wrote it himself)\n- **Topic:** The \"Tenure Trap\" in healthcare staffing; explains why agencies are used over staff pay raises due to fixed-cost explosions.\n\n**Post 6**\n- **Original Author:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment\n- **Type:** Reposted from Nava Healthcare\n- **Topic:** The \"Unsolvable Alg