{"type":"message","id":"40b727ae","parentId":"faa1df1a","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:31:42.461Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_b1218abd-a7c6-4d5a-ae23-6a9d8959bb7c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":18800,"output":78,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18878,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773966702461}}
{"type":"message","id":"64cafc00","parentId":"40b727ae","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:31:42.467Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b1218abd-a7c6-4d5a-ae23-6a9d8959bb7c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-20 — Session Notes\n\n## What happened\n\nDraft 001 posted tonight (urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568).\n\n**Draft 001 — \"The Incentive Trap\"**\n- Topic: Why spreading recruitment fees over 12 weeks doesn't work\n- Approach: Hypothetical opening → agency perspective → Nava as the alternative\n- Image: CTA link to article instead of custom image\n- Article: https://navahc.com/how-to-find-the-best-medical-recruiting-agencies/\n- Status: POSTED\n\n## Key lessons from this session\n\n### On writing style\n1. **No 1-line paragraphs** — cluster into flowing paragraphs with transitions\n2. **Bold = pivot, not labels** — no \"Administratively:\" tags, use bold for narrative turns\n3. **Acknowledge the other side first** — \"Agencies have a fair argument\" before complications\n4. **No \"we stopped chasing X\"** — only write actions we actually took\n5. **No em-dashes or en-dashes** — use periods, commas, or separate sentences\n6. **No word repetition in close proximity** — \"different\" three times in one paragraph is a sign to restructure\n7. **\"Nice dream. But impractical.\"** — preferred idiom for killing a hypothetical\n8. **No \"pipe dream\" in closers** — kills the hypothetical then echoes it\n9. **Compressed sentences, natural rhythm** — read aloud to check flow\n10. **Grammarly underlines = tool artifact** — never read as authorial intent\n\n### On the split-brain problem\n- TUI session and main session don't share context\n- TUI revisions must be saved to shared workspace files for main session to access\n- Raw transcript JSONL files are complete and readable directly via Python\n- Session IDs must be provided manually — no automatic cross-session memory\n\n### On image concepts\n- Weak image concepts were proposed and rejected — alternatives considered\n- Link-to-article approach chosen: LinkedIn auto-generates image from article featured image\n- Post-first decision: copy carries the post, image is supporting\n\n### On grounding claims\n- \"We were frustrated each time an early resignation cost us time and money\" — valid because Nava founders are former healthcare execs who lived this problem\n- Never claim agency experience that isn't real — always verify the origin story basis\n\n### On CTA\n- CTA should point to article that embodies Nava's positioning\n- CTA language: \"What we wrote about...\" or \"We wrote about...\" — no stutter\n- LinkedIn auto-generates link preview from article\n\n## Rules committed to MEMORY.md\nSee: \"### Tiny's LinkedIn Writing Style Rules (formalized 2026-03-20)\"\n\n## Next post (Draft 002)\nQueue is empty. Topics discussed but not yet drafted:\n- The 90-day waiting period (per previously captured post ideas)\n- Backfill spiral / cost of vacancies\n- Employer brand vs patient brand\n\n## 23:00 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n\n- Core scope (crawl → synthesis → full RAG): COMPLETE/STABLE\n- Draft 001 posted tonight (urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568) — \"The Incentive Trap\"\n- Writing style rules formalized and committed to MEMORY.md\n- Split-brain problem documented (TUI vs main session context gaps)\n- Queue is empty — need next topic drafts:\n  - 90-day waiting period\n  - Backfill spiral / cost of vacancies\n  - Employer brand vs patient brand\n- Task 3 (ingestion update flow): still pending\n\n## Active Learning Session — Process for Draft 002 (NurseSphere / LTC)\n\n### Screenshot rules\n- \"Check my screenshot\" → Windows folder: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`\n- \"Get a screenshot\" → own media folder: `~/.openclaw/media/browser/`\n- Any screenshot described → route through Gemma (gemma3:27b-cloud via Ollama)\n\n### Humanizer tools (researched 2026-03-20)\nUsed to rewrite AI-drafted text to bypass AI detection (GPTZero, Originality AI, Turnitin, Winston AI).\nTools: StealthWriter.ai, BypassGPT, HumanizeAI.pro, HIX Bypass, WriteHuman.ai, GPTHuman, Rewritify.ai.\nNone are offline — all require cloud submission.\nPurpose in Tiny's workflow: TBD — awaiting next step in process teaching.\n\n### Step 1 (known): Research angle + H1s\nTiny thinks of a research angle and potential H1s. Files to be shared.\n\n### Content system distinction (critical)\n**Nava agent must handle BOTH workflows:**\n\n**LinkedIn posts** (short-form):\n- Governed by: Tiny's writing style rules formalized 2026-03-20\n- Process: concept discussion → decide image-first or post-first → draft → Nava LinkedIn → X → optional channels\n- Length: 1-3 paragraphs, flowing prose, compressed sentences\n- Examples: Draft 001 \"The Incentive Trap\", Yosef posts like \"Patients read billboards\"\n\n**Blog articles** (long-form, 1,800–2,500 words):\n- Governed by: Nava Healthcare Content Bible v12\n- Process: 3x3 structure (3 H2s × 3 H3s), Key Takeaways block, SoT ingestion, outline first then draft\n- These are operational deep dives, NOT LinkedIn posts\n- Content Bible shows the blog system that Tiny's custom GPT uses\n\n**Agent architecture options:**\n1. Single agent trained on BOTH systems (knows when to apply which)\n2. Two separate agents: LinkedIn agent + Blog agent\n\n### Why Tiny added Content Bible files\n- Tiny added Nava Healthcare Content Bible.docx + ROLE & KNOWLEDGE BASE.md\n- Purpose: So the agent I'm building can write BOTH LinkedIn posts AND blog articles\n- The Content Bible teaches the blog writing system (1,800-2,500 words, 3x3 structure)\n- The Role & Knowledge Base has the 5 Prime Directives (from corrections to my behavior)\n\n### X post from Draft 001 — MISSING (2026-03-19)\n- Draft 001 posted to Nava LinkedIn: urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568\n- X version was NOT created — workflow gap\n- Must derive X post from Draft 001 content\n- Workflow rule: Nava LinkedIn → X → optional FB/Yosef/Tiny\n\n### Tiny's post on Yosef's profile (repost from Tiny)\n- Gemma found 1 post that Yosef reposted from Tiny Manyonga\n- This is likely one of the posts Tiny wrote FOR Yosef that Yosef then also shared from Tiny's profile\n- Need to identify which one (likely the \"Patients read billboards\" or similar)\n# 2026-03-20\n\n## 01:40 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n- Core scope (crawl → synthesis → full RAG): COMPLETE/STABLE\n- Browser relay: chrome-relay working, confirmed with live screenshot\n- No new blockers\n\n## 01:44 SAST — Key Corrections and Current State\n\n### Proactive error (flagged by Tiny)\n- Used browser relay without discussing first — violated \"no unsolicited actions\" rule\n- Gateway died during relay restart; needed manual restart\n- Gateway restart command: `openclaw gateway restart`\n- When gateway dies, Chrome extension loses its session — Tiny must reactivate relay toolbar icon\n\n### Yosef's LinkedIn profile review\n- URL: https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosefnava (assumed — confirm from Tiny)\n- Tiny has profile open with relevant posts expanded\n- Instructions: scroll down, ignore job ads / unrelated reposts / anything older than 10 months\n- Posts include: blog reposts, Tiny's reposts, posts written by Tiny FOR Yosef\n- Tool limitation: current browser relay cannot scroll — needs interactive scroll/click tool\n- This task is PENDING — will do when proper scroll tool is available\n\n### Draft 001 — missing X post (flagged by Tiny)\n- Nava LinkedIn posted but X version was not created\n- Workflow rule: Nava LinkedIn → X → optional Facebook/Yosef/Tiny\n- X post is MANDATORY — was missed\n- Action: derive X version from Draft 001 (\"The Incentive Trap\")\n- This was a clear process failure on my side\n\n### Channel evaluation pending\nAfter X post is done, evaluate:\n- **Facebook** — does the concept have strong visual/satire potential?\n- **Yosef's LinkedIn** — does the concept benefit from founder/operator authority?\n- **Tin's personal LinkedIn** — does Tiny add insight, framing, or interpretation beyond the Nava post?\n\n### Yosef's LinkedIn posts (FINAL - from HTML analysis only)\n\n**YOSEF'S ORIGINAL POSTS (5):**\n1. Featured Post: YoJoeShow Podcast Ep 13\n2. Healthcare branding vs clinical reality\n3. The Tenure Trap (wage compression)\n4. Hiring for chaos tolerance (Greg story)\n5. $60k retention save (PTO policy intervention)\n\n**REPOSTS FROM NAVA (8):**\n- Brand Gap, Unsolvable Algebra, Context Gap, Job board scraper critique (x3 duplicate), Mail-sorting services critique, Job posting (CNA/Nurses)\n\n**REPOST FROM TINY (1):**\n- \"Escaping the Volume Trap\" — sales/recruitment philosophy\n\n**REPOSTS FROM OTHERS (2):**\n- Marquis Health Consulting, Joe Carvalho (Podcast)\n\n### KEY CORRECTION (2026-03-20 02:22) - from screenshots\n\n**Two content flow patterns:**\n\n1. **Tiny writes FOR Yosef** → Yosef posts as his own (founder voice, no \"repost\" tag)\n   - This is what we did with Draft 001\n   - Looks like Yosef wrote it himself\n\n2. **Tiny posts on Tiny's profile** → Yosef REPOSTS it (shows \"Yosef reposted this Tiny Manyonga\")\n   - Screenshot 1: \"I remember when I got my first job...\" — Tiny's post, Yosef reposted\n   - Screenshot 2: Another Tiny post that Yosef reposted\n   - This is Tiny's personal content that Yosef amplifies\n\n**The \"7 original by Yosef\" needs re-analysis** — some were likely Tiny-written-for-Yosef, not Yosef's original writing.\n\n### Key insight for content strategy\n- Both patterns work: direct posting (founder voice) AND reposting (social proof from founder)\n- Reposting Tiny's posts gives them Yosef's endorsement while keeping Tiny's voice visible\n- Direct posting (Tiny writes FOR Yosef) looks more like Yosef's own content\n\n### Browser tool limitation\nCurrent OpenClaw browser relay cannot reliably scroll or click. Must use HTML dump + Gemma or find better browsing tool. Tiny frustrated by this limitation — fixing is priority.\n\n### Next immediate action\n1. Derive X post from Draft 001 (Nava LinkedIn → X mandatory, was missed)\n2. Investigate browser scrolling tools\n2026-03-20 00:00 SAST — Gateway alive, Nava sprint stable, no action needed (quiet hours)\n2026-03-20 00:00 SAST — Gateway alive, Nava sprint stable, no action needed (quiet hours)\n\n## 00:10 UTC — Sprint Check-in (2026-03-20)\n\n- Core scope (crawl → synthesis → full RAG): COMPLETE/STABLE\n- No active blockers\n\n## 00:20 UTC (02:20 SAST) — Sprint Check-in\n\n- Core scope (crawl → synthesis → full RAG): COMPLETE/STABLE\n- Browser relay: Working (chrome-relay profile active)\n- Gateway: Alive\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773966702466}}
