{"type":"message","id":"f858b7f3","parentId":"1d0b8eda","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:31:56.174Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-20 02:31:19 GMT+2] Compacted (41k → 3.7k) • Context 3.7k/90k (4%)\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 02:31 GMT+2] Yes, but your count of posts seems to be off for the various categories. Furthermore, what insights can you give me about my posts vs Yosef's posts vs Nava posts. Your response should be solely based on the\n HTML not the corpus or the docs I gave you. This applies only for this prompt and this response."}],"timestamp":1773966716173}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca2d1c7c","parentId":"f858b7f3","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:32:04.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_5a9376f2-f63f-441a-a4a9-de17919ef322","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\n\nhtml_path = \"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/(26) Activity _ Yosef Roston _ LinkedIn.html\"\nwith open(html_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    html = f.read()\n\n# Find all distinct author patterns\npatterns = [\n    (r'tiny.*?reposted', 'TINY_REPOST'),\n    (r'Nava.*?Healthcare.*?Recruitment', 'NAVA'),\n    (r'Yosef.*?Roston', 'YOSEF'),\n    (r'Marquis.*?Health', 'OTHER'),\n    (r'Joe.*?Carvalho', 'OTHER'),\n    (r'Yosef Roston.*?Original', 'YOSEF'),\n]\n\n# Let's extract post blocks more carefully\n# Look for the feed-shared-update pattern\nposts = re.split(r'(<li[^>]*class=\"[^\"]*feed-shared-update-v2[^\"]*\"[^>]*>)', html, flags=re.IGNORECASE)\n\nprint(f\"Found {len(posts)-1} post blocks\")\n\n# For each post block, find the author\nauthors_found = []\nfor i, block in enumerate(posts[1:], 1):\n    # Extract author name\n    author_match = re.search(r'title=\"([^\"]+)\"', block)\n    author = author_match.group(1) if author_match else \"UNKNOWN\"\n    \n    # Check for repost patterns\n    is_repost = \"reposted\" in block.lower()\n    \n    print(f\"Post {i}: Author='{author}' | Repost={is_repost}\")\n    authors_found.append((author, is_repost))\n\n# Count unique authors\nfrom collections import Counter\nprint(\"\\n--- COUNTS ---\")\nauthor_counts = Counter([a[0] for a in authors_found])\nfor author, count in author_counts.most_common():\n    print(f\"{author}: {count}\")\nPY","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":22134,"output":510,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22644,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773966724889}}
