{"type":"message","id":"4b08e558","parentId":"90ad2904","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:39:51.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Browser Capability Research Complete\n\n### Current State\n| Component | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| OpenClaw Chromium | `/usr/bin/chromium-browser` (snap) |\n| Playwright | Not installed |\n| Selenium | Not installed |\n\n### Options to Get Click/Scroll\n\n**Option A: Playwright (Recommended)**\n```bash\npip install playwright\nplaywright install chromium\n```\n- Downloads ~100MB Chromium (separate from system)\n- Full API: `page.click()`, `page.scroll()`, `page.hover()`, `page.fill()`\n- Auto-scrolls to elements before interacting\n- Works headless or headed\n\n**Option B: System Chromium + Playwright**\n```python\nbrowser = p.chromium.launch(executable_path='/usr/bin/chromium-browser')\n```\n- Reuses existing snap Chromium\n- Risk: Snap sandbox may block some operations\n\n**Option C: Selenium**\n- Older, more familiar\n- Less reliable with modern Chromium\n\n### My Recommendation\n\n**Install Playwright fresh** — cleaner, better maintained, no snap conflicts.\n\nThe OpenClaw browser relay uses CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol) which is lower-level and doesn't expose convenient click/scroll methods. Playwright is a higher-level wrapper that handles the hard stuff automatically.\n\n---\n\n**Decision needed:** Should I install Playwright now?\n\nIf yes, I'll:\n1. `pip install playwright`\n2. `playwright install chromium`\n3. Write a quick test script to verify click/scroll works\n4. Update TOOLS.md with the new capability"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":39441,"output":334,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39775,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773967191925}}
