{"type":"message","id":"6c3ebba7","parentId":"71d5c23b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:43:29.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good catch — but these are separate concerns:\n\n| Component | Location | What's at stake |\n|-----------|----------|-----------------|\n| **My environment** | WSL | Where I run (OpenClaw, tools, workspace files) |\n| **Ollama (LLM)** | Windows `localhost:11434` | My brain - powers the models I use |\n| **Playwright** | WSL (would install here) | Browser automation, not related to Ollama |\n\n**The memories live in the workspace files:**\n- `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- `MEMORY.md`\n- `rag/drafts/`, `rag/idea_bank.md`, etc.\n\nThese are WSL filesystem files — they don't live in Ollama. Installing Playwright in WSL won't touch them.\n\n**The Ollama question is separate:**\n- If you install Ollama in WSL, you'd have two Ollamas:\n  - Windows: `localhost:11434` (current)\n  - WSL: `localhost:11434` (new, after install)\n- I'd need to update my config to point to the WSL one if that's what you want\n- Or keep both and pick which model runs where\n\n**For now:** Should I install Playwright in WSL for browser automation? It won't affect:\n- Your Windows Ollama\n- Any workspace files / memories"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":39917,"output":539,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40456,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773967409427}}
