{"type":"message","id":"8259d09c","parentId":"eda29100","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:52:27.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Backed up to `~/TinyBackUp/20260320_context/`:\n- `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- `MEMORY.md`\n- `TOOLS.md`\n\n---\n\n## On Persistent Profiles\n\n**Yes, Playwright supports persistent contexts:**\n\n```python\nbrowser = p.chromium.launch_persistent_context(\n    user_data_dir=\"/path/to/profile\",  # Cookies & storage saved here\n    headless=False,  # Must be False for persistence to work well\n    ...\n)\n```\n\n**The Catch:**\n- LinkedIn is aggressive about detecting automated browsers\n- Running headless might get you flagged\n- Might need to run headed (visible browser) for login, then it persists\n- Would be a **separate profile** from your normal Chrome\n\n**Options:**\n1. **My persistent profile in WSL** — I'd launch a visible browser once, you log in, then it saves. Next run: already logged in.\n2. **Use your existing Chrome** — Point Playwright to your Windows Chrome profile (complicated in WSL)\n3. **Keep using OpenClaw relay** — It uses your logged-in Chrome, just limited interaction\n\n**My recommendation:** Option 1 — create a Playwright profile in WSL. You'd log in once (headed mode), then I'd use the saved session for future runs.\n\nWant me to set up a persistent profile now, or should I first check LinkedIn with the current setup to see what's visible?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":43636,"output":476,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44112,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773967947701}}
