{"type":"message","id":"55665893","parentId":"79dc8f55","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:04:13.759Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-20 03:01:53 GMT+2] Compacted (47k → 22k) • Context 22k/90k (24%)\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 03:03 GMT+2] Seeing the browser where, Dawn? In my windows or what? I have never even heard of via xvfb virtual display so you may have skipped some steps here."}],"timestamp":1773968653757}}
{"type":"message","id":"642193ae","parentId":"55665893","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:04:21.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right, I skipped steps. Let me clarify:\n\n**What happened:**\n- `xvfb-run` creates a *virtual* display (like a hidden monitor that doesn't actually show anywhere)\n- The browser opened in that hidden virtual display\n- You couldn't see it because there's nothing rendering to your Windows screen\n\n**You never saw it** because xvfb is headless — it has no visual output.\n\n---\n\n**Your options going forward:**\n\n**Option A: Export Chrome cookies → Playwright (recommended)**\n1. You stay in your normal Windows Chrome (already logged into LinkedIn)\n2. Run a small script in Chrome DevTools to export cookies to a file\n3. I import those cookies into Playwright\n4. Future: Playwright opens LinkedIn already logged in\n\n**Option B: Use your Windows Chrome directly**\n- The OpenClaw relay (`openclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay`) uses your Windows Chrome\n- It's already logged in\n- Limitation: Can't scroll/click (the problem we're trying to solve)\n\n**Option C: VNC viewer**\n- Install a VNC server in WSL so you could see the xvfb browser\n- More complex setup\n\n---\n\nWant to go with **Option A** (cookie export)? I'll give you a one-line script to paste into Chrome DevTools Console — it saves cookies to a file, then you share that file with me."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":40922,"output":341,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41263,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773968661885}}
{"type":"message","id":"c87d8132","parentId":"642193ae","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:07:15.215Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-20 03:07 GMT+2] Right now, I must say the VNC viewer option is very tempting because my cookie hygiene is not the best. Also, it would be useful to view what you're actually doing, don't you think? I'm leaning option C before option A. What do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773968835213}}
