{"type":"message","id":"48b7b1a5","parentId":"c6b0822f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:30:46.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it: `Profile 1` (created today at 03:29) — that's your new profile.\n\n**The problem:** Windows Chrome profiles don't work directly with Linux Chromium. They're different browser engines.\n\n**Permanent solution:** Launch Chrome in Windows with remote debugging, I'll connect from WSL via CDP and control it.\n\nRun this in Windows PowerShell or Command Prompt:\n```cmd\n\"C:\\Program Files\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\" --remote-debugging-port=9222 --user-data-dir=\"%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Profile 1\"\n```\n\nThen I'll connect from WSL. Want me to wait while you run that?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":54048,"output":299,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54347,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773970246096}}
