{"type":"compaction","id":"c6ce02b8","parentId":"f6684f60","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:39:30.442Z","summary":"## Goal\nBuild the Nava content system and agent — combining writing style rules, process knowledge, and product knowledge into a training corpus. The agent must handle BOTH LinkedIn posts AND blog articles.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- **Screenshot rule:** \"Check my screenshot\" → Windows folder (`/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`). \"Get a screenshot\" → agent's media folder (`~/.openclaw/media/browser/`). Any screenshot mention → route through Gemma for description\n- **Heartbeat intervals:** Active = 10 min (compact + memory save). Inactive = 30 min. Complex assignment = 5 min. User sign-off = backup first\n- **Grammarly underlines = tool artifact, never authorial intent**\n- **Split-brain:** TUI session and main session do not share context; must use shared workspace files\n- **Transcripts:** `sessions_history` truncates at ~15k bytes; raw JSONL at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/{id}.jsonl` are complete\n- **No unsolicited actions:** Must discuss proactive steps with Tiny before taking them\n- **Bootstrap files read-only:** MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, AGENTS.md — never overwrite during memory flush\n- **Memory file naming:** Always use canonical `YYYY-MM-DD.md` format, no timestamped variants\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Draft 001 posted to LinkedIn (urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568)\n- [x] Tiny's LinkedIn writing style rules formalized (12 rules) and committed to MEMORY.md\n- [x] Heartbeat rules updated — active/inactive intervals, sign-off backup protocol\n- [x] Split-brain problem documented\n- [x] Screenshot workflow confirmed\n- [x] Session notes written to `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- [x] Backup created at `~/TinyBackUp/20260320/`\n- [x] Corpus confirmed: 27 files mention NurseSphere, but only brand references — no substantive content\n- [x] Reclaimix identified: Nava division converting agency nurses in-building to permanent hires\n- [x] NurseSphere identified: international recruitment program + relational model\n- [x] Yosef's LinkedIn posts extracted from HTML dump (~6-8 posts)\n- [x] Agent architecture clarified: agent must do BOTH LinkedIn AND blog articles\n- [x] Browser relay setup investigated — read `BROWSER_RELAY_SETUP.md`\n- [x] Yosef LinkedIn Analysis added to `memory/2026-03-20.md` during pre-compaction flush\n- [x] Pre-compaction flush completed — appended new content, preserved bootstrap files\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Tiny teaching research and writing process\n- [ ] NurseSphere substantive content (how it works, process, differentiator) not yet in corpus\n- [ ] Draft 002 (LTC facilities + NurseSphere angle) not yet drafted\n- [ ] X post from Draft 001 still missing\n\n### Blocked\n- Cannot draft NurseSphere post without Tiny's process knowledge\n- Browser tool cannot scroll — HTML dump workaround used\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Link-to-article CTA chosen:** Draft 001 uses CTA linking to article, LinkedIn auto-generates preview\n- **Post-first over image-first:** Copy carries the post; visual is supporting\n- **NurseSphere ≠ Reclaimix:** Two distinct Nava products\n- **Draft 002 angle:** LTC facilities running short + NurseSphere as solution — requires Tiny's input\n- **Agent architecture:** Single agent trained on BOTH LinkedIn + blog, or two separate agents — Tiny to decide\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Derive X post from Draft 001 content (Nava LinkedIn → X mandatory)\n2. Investigate better browser scrolling tools\n3. Continue taking notes as Tiny teaches research and writing process\n4. Capture NurseSphere substantive content from Tiny\n5. Apply process to Draft 002 — LTC facilities angle\n6. Review `BROWSER_RELAY_SETUP.md`, `memory/2026-03-19.md`, `EMERGENCY_SAVE.md`\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Draft 001 live:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7440527552143597568\n- **Posted drafts:** `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md`\n- **Writing rules:** `MEMORY.md`\n- **Heartbeat config:** `HEARTBEAT.md`, cron job `fe4180d9-037f-413a-a1dd-c7291e5d2729`\n- **Session notes:** `memory/2026-03-20.md`\n- **Backup location:** `~/TinyBackUp/20260320/`\n- **Key gap:** No published article explains NurseSphere\n- **Yosef LinkedIn corrected counts (from HTML):** 5 original (podcast, branding vs reality, tenure trap, chaos tolerance, $60k retention), 8 reposts from Nava, 1 repost from Tiny (\"Volume Trap\"), 2 others (Marquis Health, Podcast)\n- **Key insight:** Yosef curates strategically — original = personal stories; amplifies Nava = thought leadership; brings in Tiny = niche sales/recruitment\n- **Files modified during this turn:** `memory/2026-03-20.md` (appended Yosef LinkedIn analysis)\n- **System status:** Memory compaction executed (47k → 22k tokens), context now at 22k/90k (24%)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser requested a \"pre-compaction memory flush\" — store durable memories only in `memory/2026-03-20.md` (create `memory/` directory if needed). Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files (MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, AGENTS.md) as read-only — never overwrite them. If `memory/2026-03-20.md` already exists, **append** new content only, don't overwrite. Do NOT create timestamped variant files; always use canonical `2026-03-20.md` filename.\n\n## Early Progress\nAssistant attempted to read existing file at `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md`. The read returned content showing the file already exists with substantial session notes including:\n- Draft 001 (\"The Incentive Trap\") was posted to LinkedIn\n- Detailed lessons on writing style (10+ rules about paragraph structure, bold usage, acknowledging counterpoints, sentence rhythm)\n- Notes on the \"split-brain problem\" (TUI session vs main session don't share context)\n- Notes on image concepts and grounding claims\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe memory file already contains comprehensive session notes from Mar