{"type":"message","id":"1de7c339","parentId":"0bc8ef75","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:39:37.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The browser is already running — I launched it a minute ago (session clear-cedar). It's pointing at LinkedIn Feed, but you can't see it because WSLg isn't routing the display to your Windows desktop.\n\n**The problem:** WSLg isn't working to show you the Linux browser.\n\n**Solution for seeing AND controlling:**\n\nRun this in **Windows Command Prompt** (not PowerShell):\n```cmd\n\"C:\\Program Files\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\" --remote-debugging-port=9222 --user-data-dir=\"%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Profile 1\"\n```\n\nThis opens your Windows Chrome (Profile 1) with remote debugging. Then I can:\n1. See what you're seeing\n2. Take screenshots\n3. Even control it programmatically\n\nOnce you run that command, let me know and I'll connect from WSL. You'll see the browser and can control it manually while I watch via screenshots."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":41734,"output":399,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42133,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773970777642}}
